#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.34:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.34:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga"
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.34:0.3"
msgid "34. Nidānasutta"
msgstr "34. Sources"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these three sources that give rise to deeds."

msgctxt "an3.34:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.34:1.3"
msgid ""
"Lobho nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, doso nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, moho "
"nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "Greed, hate, and delusion are sources that give rise to deeds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, lobhapakataṃ kammaṃ lobhajaṃ lobhanidānaṃ lobhasamudayaṃ, "
"yatthassa attabhāvo nibbattati tattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati."
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from greed—born, sourced, and originated from greed—"
"ripens where that new life-form is born."

#. VAR: upapajja vā → upapajje vā (bj, s1-3, km) | uppajje vā (pts1)
#. VAR: apare vā → aparāpare vā (mr)
msgctxt "an3.34:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati tattha tassa kammassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, "
"diṭṭhe vā dhamme upapajja vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And wherever that deed ripens, its result is experienced—either in the "
"present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, dosapakataṃ kammaṃ dosajaṃ dosanidānaṃ dosasamudayaṃ, "
"yatthassa attabhāvo nibbattati tattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati."
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from hate—born, sourced, and originated from hate—"
"ripens where that new life-form is born."

msgctxt "an3.34:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati tattha tassa kammassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, "
"diṭṭhe vā dhamme upapajja vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And wherever that deed ripens, its result is experienced—either in the "
"present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.135"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, mohapakataṃ kammaṃ mohajaṃ mohanidānaṃ mohasamudayaṃ, "
"yatthassa attabhāvo nibbattati tattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati."
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from delusion—born, sourced, and originated from "
"delusion—ripens where that new life-form is born."

msgctxt "an3.34:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati tattha tassa kammassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, "
"diṭṭhe vā dhamme upapajja vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And wherever that deed ripens, its result is experienced—either in the "
"present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, bījāni akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sārādāni "
"sukhasayitāni sukhette suparikammakatāya bhūmiyā nikkhittāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose some seeds were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and "
"well-kept. They’re sown in a well-prepared, productive field,"

msgctxt "an3.34:5.2"
msgid "Devo ca sammādhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya."
msgstr "and the heavens provide plenty of rain."

msgctxt "an3.34:5.3"
msgid "Evassu tāni, bhikkhave, bījāni vuddhiṃ viruḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr "Then those seeds would grow, increase, and mature."

msgctxt "an3.34:5.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yaṃ lobhapakataṃ kammaṃ lobhajaṃ lobhanidānaṃ "
"lobhasamudayaṃ, yatthassa attabhāvo nibbattati tattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, any deed that emerges from greed—born, sourced, and "
"originated from greed—ripens where that new life-form is born."

msgctxt "an3.34:5.5"
msgid ""
"Yattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati tattha tassa kammassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, "
"diṭṭhe vā dhamme upapajja vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And wherever that deed ripens, its result is experienced—either in the "
"present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:6.1"
msgid "Yaṃ dosapakataṃ kammaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Any deed that emerges from hate …"

msgctxt "an3.34:6.2"
msgid ""
"yaṃ mohapakataṃ kammaṃ mohajaṃ mohanidānaṃ mohasamudayaṃ, yatthassa "
"attabhāvo nibbattati tattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati."
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from delusion—born, sourced, and originated from "
"delusion—ripens where that new life-form is born."

msgctxt "an3.34:6.3"
msgid ""
"Yattha taṃ kammaṃ vipaccati tattha tassa kammassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, "
"diṭṭhe vā dhamme upapajja vā apare vā pariyāye."
msgstr ""
"And wherever that deed ripens, its result is experienced—either in the "
"present life, or in the next life, or in some subsequent period."

msgctxt "an3.34:6.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "These are three sources that give rise to deeds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:7.1"
msgid "Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr "Mendicants, there are these three sources that give rise to deeds."

msgctxt "an3.34:7.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.34:7.3"
msgid ""
"Alobho nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, adoso nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya, amoho "
"nidānaṃ kammānaṃ samudayāya."
msgstr ""
"Contentment, love, and understanding are sources that give rise to deeds."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:8.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, alobhapakataṃ kammaṃ alobhajaṃ alobhanidānaṃ "
"alobhasamudayaṃ, lobhe vigate evaṃ taṃ kammaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti ucchinnamūlaṃ "
"tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṅkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from contentment—born, sourced, and originated from "
"contentment—is given up when greed is done away with. It’s cut off at the "
"root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:9.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, adosapakataṃ kammaṃ adosajaṃ adosanidānaṃ adosasamudayaṃ, "
"dose vigate evaṃ taṃ kammaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ "
"anabhāvaṅkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from love—born, sourced, and originated from love—is "
"abandoned when hate is done away with. It’s cut off at the root, made like a "
"palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:10.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ, bhikkhave, amohapakataṃ kammaṃ amohajaṃ amohanidānaṃ amohasamudayaṃ, "
"mohe vigate evaṃ taṃ kammaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti ucchinnamūlaṃ tālāvatthukataṃ "
"anabhāvaṅkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from understanding—born, sourced, and originated from "
"understanding—is abandoned when delusion is done away with. It’s cut off at "
"the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the "
"future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.136"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:11.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, bījāni akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sārādāni "
"sukhasayitāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose some seeds were intact, unspoiled, not damaged by wind and sun, "
"fertile, and well-kept."

msgctxt "an3.34:11.2"
msgid "Tāni puriso agginā ḍaheyya."
msgstr "But someone would burn them with fire,"

msgctxt "an3.34:11.3"
msgid "Agginā ḍahitvā masiṃ kareyya."
msgstr "reduce them to ashes,"

#. VAR: ophuṇeyya → opuṇeyya (bj) | ophuneyya (s1-3) | opuneyya (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.34:11.4"
msgid "Masiṃ karitvā mahāvāte vā ophuṇeyya nadiyā vā sīghasotāya pavāheyya."
msgstr ""
"and sweep away the ashes in a strong wind, or float them away down a swift "
"stream."

#. VAR: anabhāvaṃkatāni → anabhāvakatāni (bj, pts1) | anabhāvaṃ katāni (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.34:11.5"
msgid ""
"Evassu tāni, bhikkhave, bījāni ucchinnamūlāni tālāvatthukatāni "
"anabhāvaṃkatāni āyatiṃ anuppādadhammāni."
msgstr ""
"Then those seeds would be cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, "
"obliterated, and unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "an3.34:11.6"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yaṃ alobhapakataṃ kammaṃ alobhajaṃ alobhanidānaṃ "
"alobhasamudayaṃ, lobhe vigate evaṃ taṃ kammaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti ucchinnamūlaṃ "
"tālāvatthukataṃ anabhāvaṃkataṃ āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, any deed that emerges from contentment—born, sourced, and "
"originated from contentment—is abandoned when greed is done away with. It’s "
"cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to "
"arise in the future."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:12.1"
msgid "Yaṃ adosapakataṃ kammaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Any deed that emerges from love …"

msgctxt "an3.34:12.2"
msgid ""
"yaṃ amohapakataṃ kammaṃ amohajaṃ amohanidānaṃ amohasamudayaṃ, mohe vigate "
"evaṃ taṃ kammaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Any deed that emerges from understanding—born, sourced, and originated from "
"understanding—is abandoned when delusion is done away with."

msgctxt "an3.34:12.3"
msgid "āyatiṃ anuppādadhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to "
"arise in the future."

msgctxt "an3.34:12.4"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi nidānāni kammānaṃ samudayāyāti."
msgstr "These are three sources that give rise to deeds.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
#. VAR: dosajañceva → dosajaṃ kammaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.34:13.1"
msgid "Lobhajaṃ dosajañceva,"
msgstr "“When an ignorant person acts"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:13.2"
msgid "mohajañcāpaviddasu;"
msgstr "out of greed, hate, or delusion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:13.3"
msgid "Yaṃ tena pakataṃ kammaṃ,"
msgstr "any deeds they have performed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:13.4"
msgid "appaṃ vā yadi vā bahuṃ;"
msgstr "—whether a little or a lot—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:13.5"
msgid "Idheva taṃ vedaniyaṃ,"
msgstr "are to be experienced right here,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:13.6"
msgid "vatthu aññaṃ na vijjati."
msgstr "not in any other place."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an3.34:14.1"
msgid "Tasmā lobhañca dosañca,"
msgstr "So a wise person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:14.2"
msgid "mohajañcāpi viddasu;"
msgstr "a mendicant arousing knowledge"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:14.3"
msgid "Vijjaṃ uppādayaṃ bhikkhu,"
msgstr "of the outcome of greed, hate, and delusion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.34:14.4"
msgid "sabbā duggatiyo jahe”ti."
msgstr "abandons all bad destinations.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.34:14.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
